		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>We present a novel feature selection algorithm for the k-means clustering problem. Our algorithm is randomized and, assuming an accuracy parameter ϵ ∈ (0, 1), selects and appropriately rescales in an unsupervised manner Θ(k log(k/ϵ)/ϵ 2) features from a dataset of arbitrary dimensions. We prove that, if we run any γ-approximate k-means algorithm (γ ≥ 1) on the features selected using our method, we can find a (1 + (1 + ϵ)γ)-approximate partition with high probability.</p>
			</abstract>
